Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: 8197d0ab8309a174385bd6bef3052ff504915d28&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="468850" author="paf0186" created="Tue, 26 Aug 2025 02:12:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I don&#8217;t think an xarray is appropriate here - that&#8217;s a highly dynamic data structure with its own locking and entries ordered by index in a complex tree, etc. &#160;The layout entries are a simple array which is dense (in terms of indices), rarely changes and has outside locking. &#160;For something like this, an xarray tree would be slower due to the indirections in the tree.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I just don&#8217;t see it as a good fit.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="468839" author="simmonsja" created="Mon, 25 Aug 2025 23:39:58 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have the cleanup done. I&apos;m working out the Xarray handling.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
